---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { products } from '../../data/products';
import type { Product } from '../../data/products';

const slugOrder = ['arlo-pro-4-spotlight', 'ring-stick-up-cam-battery', 'wyze-cam-outdoor-v2'];
const picks = slugOrder.map(slug => products.find(p => p.slug === slug)!).filter(Boolean) as Product[];
const topPick = picks[0];
---

<Layout
  title="Best Outdoor Security Camera System (2026): Arlo vs Ring vs Wyze"
  description="The best outdoor security cameras compared: Arlo Pro 4, Ring Stick Up Cam, and Wyze Cam Outdoor v2. Wire-free, battery-powered picks for every budget."
>
  <div class="bg-amber-50 border-b border-amber-100">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-2 text-xs text-amber-800 text-center">
      This site earns commissions from purchases made through our links at no extra cost to you.
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <nav class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-green-700">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      <a href="/smart-home" class="hover:text-green-700">Smart Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">›</span>
      Best Outdoor Security Camera System
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 leading-tight">
      Best Outdoor Security Camera System (2026)
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 · 3 cameras compared</p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      The outdoor security camera market has matured: battery-powered cameras now last 3–6 months per charge, 2K resolution is standard at the mid-tier, and solar panels make maintenance nearly zero. The remaining trade-offs are ecosystem compatibility, subscription cost, and image quality in low light.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      These three picks cover the premium tier (Arlo Pro 4 at $200 with 2K HDR and HomeKit support), the value tier (Ring Stick Up Cam at $100 in the Ring ecosystem), and the budget tier (Wyze Cam Outdoor v2 at $60 with no mandatory subscription).
    </p>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-100 rounded-2xl p-5 mb-10">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-sm">How many cameras do you actually need?</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Most homes are well-covered with 3–4 cameras: front door (or a video doorbell), back yard or rear entrance, side gate or driveway, and an interior garage or entry point. Cover the points of entry first. A single camera at the front door catches the majority of porch package theft and visitor activity. Add additional cameras for each additional access point you want monitored.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Top Pick Box -->
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Our Top Pick</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{topPick.name}</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-2">{topPick.tagline}</p>
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">${topPick.price}</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href={topPick.affiliateUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow noopener"
          class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap text-center"
        >
          Check Price on Amazon →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Comparison Table -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Quick Comparison</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-12 rounded-xl border border-gray-100">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Camera</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Price</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Resolution</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Night Vision</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-gray-700">Ecosystem</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {picks.map((p, i) => (
            <tr class={`border-b border-gray-100 ${i === 0 ? 'bg-green-50' : 'hover:bg-gray-50'}`}>
              <td class="p-3">
                <a href={`#${p.slug}`} class="font-medium text-gray-900 hover:text-green-700">{p.name}</a>
                {i === 0 && <span class="ml-2 text-xs bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full font-medium">Top Pick</span>}
              </td>
              <td class="p-3 font-medium">${p.price}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Resolution']}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Night Vision']}</td>
              <td class="p-3">{p.specs['Smart Platforms']}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Individual Reviews -->
    {picks.map((product, i) => (
      <section id={product.slug} class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
        <div class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">
            {i === 0 ? '🏆 Best Premium Outdoor Camera' : i === 1 ? '🥈 Best for Ring Households' : '🥉 Best Budget Outdoor Camera'}
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start justify-between gap-4">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">{product.name}</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">${product.price} &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⭐ {product.rating}/5</p>
            </div>
            <a
              href={product.affiliateUrl}
              target="_blank"
              rel="nofollow noopener"
              class="inline-block bg-green-700 text-white px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-800 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap"
            >
              Check on Amazon →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">{product.tagline}</p>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-4 mb-6">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Key Specs</p>
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8">
            {Object.entries(product.specs).map(([key, val]) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between py-1.5 border-b border-gray-100 last:border-0">
                <span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">{key}</span>
                <span class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm">{val}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-sm">Pros</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {product.pros.map(pro => (
                <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-green-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span>
                  {pro}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-sm">Cons</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {product.cons.map(con => (
                <li class="text-sm text-gray-700 flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-red-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✗</span>
                  {con}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <a
          href={product.affiliateUrl}
          target="_blank"
          rel="nofollow noopener"
          class="inline-block border border-green-700 text-green-700 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg font-semibold text-sm hover:bg-green-700 hover:text-white transition-colors"
        >
          Buy {product.name} on Amazon →
        </a>
      </section>
    ))}

    <!-- Buying Guide -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Outdoor Camera Buying Guide</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Color night vision vs infrared night vision</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Traditional infrared night vision produces black-and-white footage — fine for detecting movement, poor for identifying clothing color or vehicle color in security incidents. Color night vision uses a built-in spotlight or very sensitive image sensor to capture full color in darkness. The Arlo Pro 4's integrated spotlight triggers on motion and produces vivid color night footage. The Ring Stick Up Cam uses infrared — good for detection, not for color identification. The Wyze Outdoor's color night vision is sensor-based and works best in areas with some ambient light.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Solar panels: which cameras support them</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">All three cameras are compatible with solar panels that eliminate battery charging entirely in sunny climates. Arlo has its own Arlo Solar Panel ($25–$30). Ring offers Ring Solar Panel ($25) and Ring Solar Stick Up Cam as a bundle. Wyze has the Wyze Solar Panel (~$20). Each panel connects magnetically or via cable to the camera. In most climates with 4+ hours of direct sun per day, a solar panel keeps the battery at 80–100% indefinitely. Factor this into your total cost — it's often worth adding for cameras in hard-to-reach locations.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Subscription cost reality check</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">Hardware prices are the visible cost; subscriptions are the ongoing one. Arlo Secure is $8–$10/month per camera or $25/month for up to 5. Ring Protect Basic is $4/month per camera or $10/month unlimited devices. Wyze Cam Plus is $2/month per camera (or $10/month for all devices). Without subscriptions: Arlo shows live view only, Ring shows live view only, Wyze shows event clips (14 days free via AWS) plus live view. If subscription cost concerns you, Wyze offers the best functionality without a plan.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I mix cameras from different brands?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Yes — you can mix brands, but each will use its own app for recording and history. For voice control, all three work with Alexa and Google Home, so you can view live feeds and get motion alerts through a unified voice assistant. For unified recording in one app, stick with one brand. If you already have Ring doorbells, adding Ring Stick Up Cams keeps everything in one Ring app.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What's the typical battery life for outdoor cameras?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">At moderate motion volume (10–20 events per day), expect: Arlo Pro 4 — 3 to 6 months; Ring Stick Up Cam — 3 to 6 months; Wyze Cam Outdoor v2 — 3 to 6 months. Battery life drops dramatically with high-traffic areas (busy driveways, street-facing cameras), frequent live view access, and cold weather. A solar panel eliminates the charging concern entirely for cameras in sun-exposed locations.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Are outdoor cameras weatherproof enough for all climates?</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">All three cameras are IP65-rated (Arlo Pro 4, Wyze Outdoor) or IP55-rated (Ring Stick Up Cam), meaning they're fully protected against dust and resistant to rain jets. They handle temperatures from about -4°F to 113°F. Extended exposure to direct freezing rain or temperatures below -20°F can affect battery performance but won't damage the camera electronics. In very harsh climates, place cameras under an eave for added protection.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Guides -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-100 pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/smart-home/best-smart-doorbell-camera" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Smart Home</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Smart Doorbell Camera →</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/smart-home/best-smart-camera-for-apartments" class="group block border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-4 hover:border-green-200 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <p class="text-xs text-green-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">Smart Home</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-gray-900 text-sm group-hover:text-green-700 transition-colors">Best Smart Security Camera for Apartments →</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>
